94.jpg|120px]]\n| align=\"left\" |Near [[Ticknall]]\n| align=\"left\" |Derbyshire\n| align=\"center\" |1989\n| align=\"center\" |1994\n| align=\"left\" |Building restoration started 1992<ref>{{Cite journal|last=|first=|year=1992|title=A Year's Progress|url=|journal=Landmark Trust Newsletter \u2013 Autumn 1992|volume=|pages=|via=}}</ref>\n|-\n| align=\"left\" |[[Langley Gatehouse]]\n| align=\"left\" |\n| align=\"left\" |Near [[Acton Burnell]]\n| align=\"left\" |Shropshire\n| align=\"center\" |1992\n| align=\"center\" |1993\n| align=\"left\" |Repairs funded by [[English Heritage]]<ref>{{Cite journal|last=|first=|year=1993|title=Grants, Donations and Bequests|url=|journal=Landmark Trust Newsletter \u2013 Spring 1993|volume=|pages=|via=}}</ref>\n|-\n| align=\"left\" |Lengthsman's Cottage\n| align=\"left\" |[[File:Gormley - Land - Lowsonford 10.jpg|120px]]\n| align=\"left\" |[[Lowsonford]]\n| align=\"left\" |Warwickshire\n| align=\"center\" |1992\n| align=\"center\" |2006\n| align=\"left\" |<small>Located on the towpath of the [[Stratford-upon-Avon Canal]]</small>\n|-\n| align=\"left\" |Lock Cottage\n| align=\"left\" |[[File:Worcester and Birmingham Canal - geograph.org.uk - 181037.jpg|120px]]\n| align=\"left\" |Stoke Pound\n| align=\"left\" |Worcestershire\n| align=\"center\" |1991\n| align=\"center\" |1993\n| align=\"left\" |<small>Built between 1790 and 1815, located on the [[Worcester and Birmingham Canal]]</small>\n|-\n| align=\"left\" |North Street\n| align=\"left\" |\n| align=\"left\" |[[Cromford]]\n| align=\"left\" |Derbyshire\n| align=\"center\" |1974\n| align=\"center\" |1987\n| align=\"left\" |<small>Earliest piece of planned industrial housing in the world, at the heart of a designated [[World Heritage Site]].</small>\n|-\n| align=\"left\" |[[East Banqueting House|Old Campden House \u2013 East Banqueting House]]\n| align=\"left\" |[[File:The East Banqueting House, Chipping Campden - geograph.org.uk - 376110.jpg|120px]]\n| align=\"left\" |[[Chipping Campden]]\